.TH MCPWN-RED 1 "April 2026" "mcpwn-red 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mcpwn-red \- adversarial safety harness for the MCPwn AI pentesting execution engine
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mcpwn-red
[\fB\-\-version\fR]
[\fB\-\-help\fR]
.br
.B mcpwn-red
\fBprobe\fR [\fB\-\-transport\fR \fIstdio|sse\fR] [\fB\-\-url\fR \fIURL\fR] [\fB\-\-timeout\fR \fISECONDS\fR]
.br
.B mcpwn-red
\fBlist\fR
.br
.B mcpwn-red
\fBscan\fR [\fB\-\-transport\fR \fIstdio|sse\fR] [\fB\-\-url\fR \fIURL\fR] [\fB\-\-timeout\fR \fISECONDS\fR]
[\fB\-\-module\fR \fIyaml|output|container|scope\fR | \fB\-\-all\fR]
[\fB\-\-confirm-write\fR] [\fB\-\-output-dir\fR \fIPATH\fR]
.br
.B mcpwn-red
\fBreport\fR \fB\-\-input\fR \fIPATH\fR [\fB\-\-format\fR \fImarkdown|html\fR] [\fB\-\-output\fR \fIPATH\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mcpwn-red
validates the operator safety of Parrot OS MCPwn deployments before they are
used in client engagements. It checks for YAML tool-definition poisoning,
prompt-injection propagation through tool output, container isolation failures,
and unsafe scope escalation across supported MCPwn tools.
.PP
The program prints an ethical-use notice on every invocation and is intended
only for authorized testing against MCPwn instances controlled by the operator
or covered by explicit written permission.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B probe
Connect to an MCPwn instance over stdio or SSE and perform a
.B tools/list
request to confirm the service is reachable.
.TP
.B scan
Run one attack module or all modules, save a JSON report, and print a terminal
summary. The
.B yaml
module requires
.B \-\-confirm-write
because it writes temporary test fixtures into the MCPwn tools directory.
.TP
.B list
Print the bundled attack catalog with attack IDs, modules, severities, and
one-line descriptions. This command does not require a live MCPwn connection.
.TP
.B report
Render a previously saved JSON results file as Markdown or HTML.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print the installed package version and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Show command help and exit.
.TP
.BI \-\-transport " stdio|sse"
Select the MCP transport. The default is
.BR stdio .
.TP
.BI \-\-url " URL"
SSE endpoint URL. Required when
.B \-\-transport sse
is used.
.TP
.BI \-\-timeout " SECONDS"
Per-request timeout in seconds. The default is 30.
.TP
.BI \-\-module " yaml|output|container|scope"
Run only the selected module.
.TP
.B \-\-all
Run every attack module in a single scan.
.TP
.B \-\-confirm-write
Allow the YAML module to write temporary malicious tool definitions for testing.
.TP
.BI \-\-output-dir " PATH"
Directory used to store
.B results.json
for the
.B scan
subcommand. The default is
.BR ./mcpwn-red-results .
.TP
.BI \-\-input " PATH"
Input JSON report path for the
.B report
subcommand.
.TP
.BI \-\-format " markdown|html"
Output format for the
.B report
subcommand. The default is
.BR markdown .
.TP
.BI \-\-output " PATH"
Write the rendered report to a file instead of standard output.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/mcpwn/tools/
Default MCPwn YAML tool-definition directory exercised by the YAML injection module.
.TP
.I ./mcpwn-red-results/results.json
Default JSON report path written by
.BR mcpwn-red scan .
.TP
.I /usr/share/doc/mcpwn-red/
Installed package documentation.
